				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> should a mage choose to calculate their dps vs. the dps of a mob</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I am not trying to compare the magicians DPS vs the MOBs DPS, I am comparing a magicians HPS (heal per second) to the MOBs DPS.
<br />

<br />
If a MOBs DPS is less than or equal too the magicians HPS the magician can combat this foe indefinitely as long as he has mana to cast heals.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Therefore, a level 65 magician can combat any MOB that has a DPS lower than 140.00 as long as he has mana. 
