			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Aamen, you missed the whole point of this info thread.
<br />

<br />
-Nobody was telling mages to kill mobs using heals.
<br />
-Nobody was saying healing pets back to back is the preferred way to kill.
<br />
-Nobody claimed that mobs have perfectly stable DPS.
<br />

<br />
This thread <span style="font-weight: bold">was made to let a mage know what his tools are, and its up to the mage to choose what to do in what situation.</span>
<br />

<br />
If you solo a level 59 summoning mob, with high DPS, very resistant to all spells, and lots of HPS (ex: The Cliff Golem).  Chain healing a pet might be your only method.  Or if your MT dies, pet takes aggro and you need to keep him alive while other casters burn down the mob, knowing what your healing per second is helps.  You seemed to look at this thread as if I or somebody else was telling mages to fight only using back to back heals, and you're dispelling a myth about how good they are.  But you entirely missed the point, which was this is just good info for a mage to know so he can choose when to heal and when not to.
<br />

<br />
About your comment on non-consistant DPS.  I should refer you to monks, and WHY they got nerfed.  Before the nerf, a monk could tank BETTER OVERALL then a Warrior, but his damage taken was too incosistant.  A cleric could not plan his CH with enough time to estimate when its good to start healing.  Then when some monks had uberest of uber gear, and they had enough HP to "even out" the non-consistant damage, then it was no longer a problem.  The only issue at that time, was the "Average" DPS over time.  Since that was BETTER then a Warrior, guilds were using monks as Main Tanks, thus... the nerf.
<br />

<br />
But learn from that...  The same logic applies to pets.  If your pet has 6k HP (65 earth + Virtue) and the mob your fighting varies from 40 DPS to 180 DPS, but his over time average is 130 DPS.  Then you <span style="font-weight: bold">can fight him and maintain your pets HP using 64 heal and 60 heal</span> just like this thread says you can.
<br />

<br />
Get the idea?<br />_________________<br /><Center><bold>
<br />
Sage Eandori Raintree</bold>
<br />
63 Arch Mage
<br />
The Blinding, Rooting, Epic pet casting, gimp mage of Solusek Ro!
<br />
<a href= "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=36994">what does a solo mage at 63 wear?</a>
<br />
</center></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
